### Time to make it fancier! üíÖ

Let‚Äôs put those boring and flat sections inside a colorful carousel! Because who doesn‚Äôt love them?

In order to save time, I decided to use an existing carousel component built by the community. For this demo, I used [`react-swipeable-views-native`](https://github.com/oliviertassinari/react-swipeable-views). I‚Äôm sure there must be better alternatives out there, but this one was the perfect match for my needs.

Also, in order to generate nice random colors, I used [`randomcolor`](https://github.com/davidmerfield/randomColor).

Install both libraries as dependencies for the project:

```bash
~ yarn add react-swipeable-views-native randomcolor
```

Then I made a few modifications inside `App.js`‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääyou can find the code [here](https://github.com/EmaSuriano/e2e-react-native-detox/blob/master/App.js). This is the summary of changes:

- Wrap all the sections inside `SwipeableViews` to enable swiping behavior
- Wrap each section inside a custom `View` called `Slide` that implements properties like `padding` and `backgroundColor`
- Add a `Button` and a `TextInput` component to the last two slides

